## (1) English Translation

Marquis Wu of Wei planned affairs appropriately, and none of his ministers could match him. When he left court, he had a pleased expression. Wu Qi advanced and said: "Has Your Majesty ever heard from your attendants the words of King Zhuang of Chu?" The Marquis said: "What were the words of King Zhuang of Chu?" Wu Qi replied: "King Zhuang of Chu planned affairs appropriately, and none of his ministers could match him. When he left court, he had a worried expression. Shen Gong Wuchen came forward and asked: 'Why does Your Majesty have a worried expression after court?' The King said: 'I planned affairs appropriately, and none of my ministers could match me—this is why I worry. As the saying in the *Zhonglu* states: "A ruler who finds a teacher among the nobles becomes a true king; one who finds a friend becomes a hegemon; one who finds someone to question him survives; one who plans for himself and finds none to match him will perish." Now, with my lack of virtue, and none of my ministers able to match me—my state is nearly doomed! This is why I worry.' King Zhuang of Chu worried, yet Your Majesty rejoices." Marquis Wu hesitated, then bowed twice and said: "Heaven has sent you, Master, to correct my fault."

